{"created":"2026-06-03T17:42:55.521Z","created_by_ref":"identity--ab072f15-9b87-4ee1-898f-b584d41f29b0","description":"A large-scale operation impersonates open-source and freeware projects to capture search traffic, targeting tools such as Ghidra, dnSpy, and SpiderFoot. The professionally designed sites load CloudFront-hosted JavaScript that converts download button clicks into handoffs to a Traffic Distribution System (TDS), which enforces strict gating including first-visit state, click confirmation, anti-bot logic, VPN filtering, and frequency capping. The ecosystem appears primarily built for traffic acquisition and monetization using legitimate ad-tech, but downstream redirect chains repeatedly led selected users to malware delivery infrastructure. The observed payloads include SessionGate (a multi-stage loader with heavy obfuscation delivering potentially unwanted applications), RemusStealer (an infostealer targeting over 20 browsers and hundreds of extensions), and AnimateClipper (a cryptocurrency clipper supporting 20+ blockchain ecosystems). Over 5,000 VirusTotal submissions indicate substantial reach across the ...","id":"report--893ba5ff-bd04-467c-9707-bdfcab8ae511","labels":["threat-report"],"modified":"2026-06-04T09:08:20.130Z","name":"Impersonation, Click Hijacking, and TDS: Inside a Malware Distribution Ecosystem","object_refs":["identity--ab072f15-9b87-4ee1-898f-b584d41f29b0","indicator--3275b92c-774b-4704-b6c1-427a8b1d4241","indicator--02897ac5-33c1-4350-8965-cac083f27c3d","indicator--785c6e75-4c4f-449d-8186-5df7d39372e8","indicator--1c4cf00e-54b2-40e4-b57a-65544bd1f074","indicator--71c2ced6-331f-48e1-b707-6237f3eb587d","indicator--48cf28b5-daa1-4451-ac68-b420ce723929","indicator--3fc5b356-31a0-435b-8ac5-dc5ca2b89024","indicator--a8f36e87-107b-4258-8582-23ec5b4acb3d","indicator--455f45cc-724e-4d89-b651-6c060f8c13be","indicator--b156cc95-ac92-42f9-b9d8-578c2aa33e12","indicator--28c284e9-cde9-4a03-aac8-fe2946c067a9","indicator--0b21f050-f5db-4a3d-ba0